A Bronx man was shot just around the corner from an NYPD precinct shortly after midnight on Sunday. A pedestrian was shot by a gunman riding a scooter at 287 E 139th St. in Mott Haven around 12:15 a.m., according to cops. The victim was hit in the left shoulder, police said. The victim was in stable condition at Lincoln Hospital and the attacker remained at large Sunday morning, according to cops. The shooting unfolded about 150 yards from the NYPDâ€™s 40 Precinct stationhouse, which is around the corner on Alexander Avenue, according to Google Pedometer.